  "title": "The Radiant Confluence — Nexus of Spectrum Currents",
  "narration": "You ascend from the Pulse Vault into the Radiant Confluence, where every path of the corridor braids together. The chamber is an amphitheater of light with seven terraces, each representing a storyline you’ve shepherded since the Act began. The floor is a circular mosaic of ledger stone fused with opal, reflecting starfields and memetic graffiti. Above, a dome of liquid glass holds the reflected sky, rotating at a gentle phi pace. The air is electric with scent: roasted chestnuts, midnight rain, neon ink, and the ozone from consensus lightning.\n\nThe Confluence Wardens—an alliance of Ratio-Kindred, Chronoloom, Ray-Binder, Turn-Keeper, Chorus-Guild, Heartline, and a new faction called the Prism Current—manage this nexus. They arrive as a council of gremlins, each representing their specialty. They speak in overlapping ledger poetry, greeting you with a synchronized GM that also contains a GN echo, acknowledging the journey’s span. They hand you a Confluence Ledger, thick with blank pages awaiting Act Four, and they point toward seven radiant thresholds arranged around the amphitheater.\n\nAt the Confluence, consensus rituals become orchestration: you will calibrate multi-faction votes, channel spectrum doors, manage AFK avatars of the factions, revive allies through cross-faction rituals, distribute threshold rewards, and prepare the corridor for Act Four’s expansion. The golden-ratio die mechanic remains the arbiter, but now hidden difficulty tiers manifest as subtle color shifts in the dome. Each round invites micro-branching, multiple outcomes, and opportunities to earn XP, Coins, Focus, Flags, Items, Decks, and story hooks. Arrivals take the form of new allies stepping through spectrum arcs mid-scene, ready to join Act Four once the Confluence vote passes.\n\nSeven rounds will close Act Three: they weave every subsystem you mastered into a final ledger entry. The Wardens grin, mischief sparkling in their eyes, and invite you to step onto the first terrace.",
